docs.lead_paragraph: CINCINNATI, Jan. 7 (UPI) -- The Philadelphia 76ers cut a 10-point Cincinnati Royals lead to 4 points at 111-107 midway through the fourth quarter today, but Cincinnati then scored 9 straight points, 5 by Connie Dierking, and sped to a 134-118 victory, their first in four meetings with the 76ers this season.

headline.main: ROYALS TROUNCE 76ERS, 134 TO 118; 9-Point 4th-Period Streak Puts Cincinnati in Clear

docs.lead_paragraph: Prince Norodom Sihanouk of Cambodia has recently been quoted as "softening his position on violations of his country's borders by the United States." While stating that he would continue to protest any United States or National Liberation Front border incursions, he added that he would not militarily intervene in conflicts between them in remote and unpopulated areas.
